        <p>The materials available at this web site are for informational purposes only and not for the purpose of providing legal advice. You should not contact your attorney to obtain advice with respect to any particular issue or problem. Use of and access to this Web site or any of the email links contained within the site do not create an attorney-client relationship between The Law Office of Ebert Haegele and the user or browser.</p>

        <h3>2. No Guarantee of Results</h3>
        <p>Representative cases and past results mentioned on this website "The Prosecutor's Advantage" or "Experience" sections correspond to the attorney's past experience as a prosecutor or defense attorney. <strong>Past results do not guarantee future outcomes.</strong> Every criminal case is unique and depends on the specific facts and laws applicable to that case.</p>

        <h3>3. Jurisdiction</h3>
        <p>The Law Office of Ebert Haegele practices primarily in <strong>Kentucky</strong> (Jefferson County, Oldham County, Bullitt County, Shelby County) and the United States District Court for the Western District of Kentucky. The firm does not seek to represent anyone desiring representation based upon viewing this website in a state where this website fails to comply with all laws and ethical rules of that state.</p>

